===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# {{lb|en|Judaism}} The [[anniversary]] of a [[person]]'s death, usually a [[parent#Noun|parent]]'s, often [[mark#Verb|marked]] by the [[light#Verb|lighting]] of a [[memorial#Adjective|memorial]] [[candle]] and other [[ritual]]s.
#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Richard Wheatley|title=The Jews in New York.—II.|magazine=[[w:The Century Magazine|The Century Illustrated Magazine]]|location=New York, N.Y.|publisher=[[w:The Century Company|The Century Co.]]; London: [[w:T. Fisher Unwin|T[homas] Fisher Unwin]]|month=February|year=1892|volume=XLIII|issue=4|page=516|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/centuryillustrat43newyuoft/page/516/mode/1up|oclc=692496497|passage="'''Yahrzeit'''" (year's time) is the anniversary of the parent's death. On the evening preceding, a light is kindled in the house, and kept burning until the following sundown. Synagogue service in the morning and evening is also attended, and the kaddish recited. "Nahala" (inheritance) is the poetic equivalent of the Spanish and Portuguese Jews for the Teutonic '''Yahrzeit'''.}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Leon Spitz|title=[[w:Tisha B'Av|Tisha b’Ab]]—The yahrzeit of every Jew|newspaper=[[w:Canadian Jewish Review|The Canadian Jewish Chronicle]]|location=Montreal, Que.|publisher=The Eagle Publishing Company|date=1 August 1930|page=1|pageurl=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=pe5OAAAAIBAJ&sjid=9ksDAAAAIBAJ&pg=2415%2C753135|issn=0384-9775|oclc=937495816|passage=Sad to say, the '''Yahrzeit''' of every-Jew is fading away from the memory of the average Jew in America.}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Leon Wieseltier|authorlink=Leon Wieseltier|title=A Year Later|url=https://newrepublic.com/article/66433/year-later|editor={{w|Peter Beinart}}|magazine={{w|The New Republic}}|location=New York, N.Y.|publisher=The Republic Publishing Company|date=2 September 2002|issn=0028-6583|oclc=648332520|passage=The '''yahrzeit''' is here, and the least lachrymose country on earth is devising its rituals of commemoration.}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Irwin Cohen|title=Hank Greenberg’s 30th yahrzeit|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170113115331/http://www.jewishpress.com/sections/sports/baseball-insider/hank-greenbergs-30th-yahrzeit/2016/08/10/|archivedate=13 January 2017|newspaper={{w|The Jewish Press}}|location=New York, N.Y.|publisher=The Jewish Press|date=10 August 2016|issn=0021-6674|oclc=992639836|passage=Let's remember {{w|Hank Greenberg}}'s '''''yahrzeit''''', the 30th of Av, which falls this year on Sept. 3.}}
